<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="255" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[843,1494,459,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
Annual, robust herbaceous plant which can reach up to 1.5 m in height; lives in 
<collectingCountry box="[1073,1157,492,516]" name="Bolivia" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1167,1269,492,516]" name="Paraguay" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1323,1435,492,516]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, with the Gran 
<collectingRegion box="[942,1010,524,548]" country="Argentina" name="Chaco" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Chaco</collectingRegion>
and its adjoining areas being places where its presence has been well documented (TOLEDO &amp; BARBOSA, 2005: 73-76). It lives in clearings and the edges of forests, invading crops, roadsides and disturbed terrain. The Pilagá report that the ripe fruit is a source of food.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
